description:
## Location
firmware/bridge-zephyr/subsys/lichen/lichen_l2.c:302

## Issue
lichen_l2_send() validates pkt for NULL (line 307-310) but does not validate iface:

```c
static int lichen_l2_send(struct net_if *iface, struct net_pkt *pkt)
{
    int ret;

    /* Validate pkt parameter (project-LICHEN-1www.22) */
    if (pkt == NULL) {
        LOG_ERR("TX rejected: pkt is NULL");
        return -EINVAL;
    }
    // ... no iface validation
```

Meanwhile, lichen_l2_recv() and lichen_l2_enable() both validate iface for NULL with explicit issue references (project-LICHEN-1www.25).

## What goes wrong
- Inconsistent validation policy across L2 callbacks
- If Zephyr ever calls send() with NULL iface (unlikely but possible during teardown), undefined behavior
- Pattern suggests iface validation was considered important (added to recv/enable) but missed for send

## Fix
Either:
1. Add iface NULL validation to match recv/enable, or
2. Add a comment explaining why send does not validate iface (e.g., caller guarantee)
